Great stuff.

This shade is clear with a touch of sparkle, so it's perfect on its own or layered over your fave lip liner or lipstick. I've been keeping it in my bag 24/7‚Äîit's that go-to product that makes you feel instantly put together.

faceoff_positive.comments:
The Glow Reviver Lip Oil Glimmer is a fantastic addition to your makeup bag for a casual gloss. It is super shiny! The Chocoluxe tint looks super dark online, but in person it's a lighter color, and it goes on very sheer. The scent is sweet! The sheer color really seems like it would complement most complexions- I'm pretty fair skinned and thought it would be too dark for me, but it goes on like a sheer silk. It's really very pretty. I kind of wish it had a little more color, but being a lip oil it's perfect for a sheer gloss. The sheerness of the color also allows for ease of application without worrying about perfect lines, so that places this firmly in my purse for quick and casual wear.

The texture is a little sticky, but not too much-- just what you would expect with natural oils like apricot and jojoba. It's comfortable, I just wouldn't go kissing any cheeks with it. It left my lips feeling pretty soft, though it could use better staying power, it was lasting maybe 20min while talking, and about 45mins when at rest. The xxl applicator is plush and soft, it felt very strange at first, but effective, I really liked it.

The packaging is gorgeous, from the box to the bottle, it screams glam. The box and bottle are both also easy to open.

It reminds me a lot of some  similar products from competitors, so I'd say overall it's on par with them, perhaps a little higher. It could use a little more color and it is a little sticky IMO, but it feels like a very good quality, well above its price point. Definitely something you won't regret choosing.
faceoff_positive.headline: Chocoluxe is so pretty! You won't regret it.

faceoff_negative.comments:
My first impression of this lip oil is the beautiful plush lip applicator. Love love LOVE. It hugs the lips perfectly. AND that it smells like mint! I'm not a fan of my lip products having a scent. It is not as powerful as the Patrick Ta sparkly lip plumper cinammon scent that has that lasting power, which can be overwhelming (especially if youre not in the mood.) If you enjoy a subtle hint of a minty scent, you'd enjoy this! 

I enjoy that the product is not sticky and if your hair so happens to fly around with the wind, you won't have a goppy mess all over your face!Considering i bought this product mid December, my lips are parched and in need of that extra hydration during the day time (and not just at night). 

If you're like me and don't want to constantly reapply your lip products and need the extra hydration, i don't recommend you use this alone. 

I think this product would make a GREAT lip topper and stocking stuffer! If you're like me this time of year, I recommend using a lip mask/hydrating lipstick then putting this lip oil on top to add that POP of sparkle VERSUS using alone with a lip liner. 

I only give this product THREE STARS because its not as hydrating as I was expecting for a lip oil and i don't like my lippies to have any scent considering thats my preference and any bit of fragrance isn't ideal for me. I LIKE but I DON'T love! 

Remember makeup is PERSONAL. Everyone is different! It's a matter of trying it and seeing if it's YOUR IT lippie. 

Disclaimer: I have asthma and allergies year round. My preference with ALL makeup and skincare products is no fragrance/scent.
faceoff_negative.headline: I like but I don't LOVE
